Consider a satellite of mass  \(m\)  in a circular orbit of radius  \(r\) .<br><br>Since&nbsp;\(v^2=\frac{GM}{r}\)<br><ul><li>The&nbsp;<b>kinetic energy</b>&nbsp;\(E_k=\frac{1}{2}mv^2=\frac{GMm}{2r}\)</li></ul><ul><li>The&nbsp;<b>potential energy</b>&nbsp;\(E_p=mV=-\frac{GMm}{r}\)</li></ul><ul><li>The&nbsp;<b>total energy</b>&nbsp;\(E=E_k+E_p=\frac{GMm}{2r}\)</li></ul>